Context:
* The course is called Degree Preparation.
* It is held at George Brown College's St. James "A" building located at 200 King Street East.
* The duration of the course is 15 weeks.
* The sessions for this course are offered Tuesday to Thursday from 9 am to 12 pm.
* For more information, interested individuals can email gbcdegreebridging@georgebrown.ca or call (416) 415-5000 ext. 3683.
* The U-Level Bridging program related information is also available.
* Applicants can sign up to receive updates on application deadlines, college news, upcoming events, tours and more.
* Contact George Brown College via phone at 416-415-2000 or TTY: 1-877-515-5559, or email ask.george@georgebrown.ca.
* Visit the college's social media hub for more information.
* The information on the website is subject to change without notice.
